# Core Package Rules

## Responsibilities

- `scanner.ts` — orchestrates scan pipeline
- `project-detect.ts` — reads package.json, detects Vue/Vite/Pinia/Nuxt
- `sfc-parser.ts` — wraps @vue/compiler-sfc
- `import-graph.ts` — builds component/file import graph
- `score.ts` — health score calculation (formula in docs/02-feature-plan.md)
- `reporter/` — terminal + JSON output
- `types.ts` — shared Issue, Rule, ScanContext interfaces

## Constraints

- core MUST NOT import from packages/rules (rules depend on core, not reverse)
- core MUST NOT contain rule-specific detection logic
- Export public API from `packages/core/src/index.ts`
- JSON report must include `schemaVersion: 1` — bump on breaking changes

## ScanContext

Build once in scanner, pass to all rules. Rules must be pure functions of ScanContext.

```typescript
interface ScanContext {
  root: string;
  vueFiles: VueFileInfo[];
  tsProject: Project;
  importGraph: ImportGraph;
  projectMeta: ProjectMeta;
}
```
